Regent Investment Management LLC Boosts Stake in Merck & Company, Inc. (NYSE:MRK)

Posted by David Goldstein on Jul 27th, 2017 // No Comments 

Regent Investment Management LLC raised its position in Merck & Company, Inc. (NYSE:MRK) by 4.3% during the second quarter, according to its most recent filing with the Securities and Exchange Commission (SEC). The fund owned 38,873 shares of the company’s stock after buying an additional 1,600 shares during the period. Regent Investment Management LLC’s holdings in Merck & were worth $2,492,000 as of its most recent filing with the SEC. 
Several other large investors have also bought and sold shares of the company. Norges Bank acquired a new stake in Merck & during the fourth quarter worth $1,628,824,000. Dodge & Cox acquired a new stake in Merck & during the fourth quarter worth $821,068,000. Asset Management One Co. Ltd. raised its stake in Merck & by 992.4% in the fourth quarter. Asset Management One Co. Ltd. now owns 4,936,317 shares of the company’s stock worth $290,682,000 after buying an additional 4,484,427 shares in the last quarter. DZ BANK AG Deutsche Zentral Genossenschafts Bank Frankfurt am Main acquired a new stake in Merck & during the fourth quarter worth $252,822,000. Finally, Bank of Montreal Can raised its stake in Merck & by 49.7% in the first quarter. Bank of Montreal Can now owns 8,991,093 shares of the company’s stock worth $571,295,000 after buying an additional 2,983,319 shares in the last quarter. Institutional investors own 73.80% of the company’s stock. 


 Get Merck & Company Inc. alerts:



Merck & Company, Inc. (NYSE MRK) traded up 3.180% on Thursday, reaching $63.765. 17,531,099 shares of the company traded hands. Merck & Company, Inc. has a 1-year low of $57.18 and a 1-year high of $66.80. The stock has a market capitalization of $174.41 billion, a price-to-earnings ratio of 40.641 and a beta of 0.81. The stock’s 50-day moving average is $63.67 and its 200-day moving average is $63.69. 




Merck & (NYSE:MRK) last announced its earnings results on Tuesday, May 2nd. The company reported $0.88 earnings per share (EPS) for the quarter, beating the consensus estimate of $0.83 by $0.05. The company had revenue of $9.43 billion during the quarter, compared to analyst estimates of $9.25 billion. Merck & had a net margin of 15.32% and a return on equity of 24.99%. The firm’s quarterly revenue was up 1.3% compared to the same quarter last year. During the same period in the previous year, the business posted $0.89 earnings per share. Equities research analysts expect that Merck & Company, Inc. will post $3.85 EPS for the current year. 
The firm also recently announced a quarterly dividend, which will be paid on Friday, October 6th. Investors of record on Friday, September 15th will be given a dividend of $0.47 per share. The ex-dividend date of this dividend is Thursday, September 14th. This represents a $1.88 annualized dividend and a yield of 3.04%. Merck &’s dividend payout ratio (DPR) is 85.84%. 
